It was a celebration galore this afternoon at the Presidential Villa as the Guards brigade organised a special parade to mark President Muhammadu Buhariâ€™s 76th birthday. The parade by 203 soldiers and eight officers was organised at the forecourt of the Presidential Villa. The parade started when the President arrived the venue at 12.22pm. After the parade, the event was climaxed by the cutting of the birthday cake by the President at 12.48pm. He was assisted by dignitaries present including the SGF, Chief of Staff, Service Chiefs, ministers among others. Cards were presented by the Chief of Staff, SGF, Guards brigade commandant and Minister of Defence to the President for his 76th birthday. Buhari protests reduction of his age at birthday parade At birthday parade: Buhari protests reduction of his age Guards treat Buhari to colourful parade at 73